<h2>About Throwdowns</h2>
<p>Throwdowns are challenges in APO where two small groups compete in one of 5 categories. Those categories are:
	<ul>
		<li>Most office hours</li>
		<li>Best score on quizzes</li>
		<li>Most L, F, or S points accumulated</li>
		<li>Greatest total number of kindnappings in a week</li>
		<li>Most money raised for a fundraiser </li>
	</ul>
</p>
<p>	Small groups wager points and the winning group takes the loser's points. One small group can challenge another in any of the above 5 categories.</p>

<br>

<h2>Rules for Throwdowns:</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Throwdowns begin as soon as they've been accepted by both groups. They end at 11:59pm on Friday.</li>
	<li>Small Groups can wager any number of points between 10 and 50.</li>
	<li>Small Groups can challenge multiple groups in the same week as long as the total points wagered doesn't exceed 50.</li>
	<li>Possible methods of challenges are listed in the about section above.</li>
	<ul>
		<li>For office hour throwdowns, there will be a list on the office door for people to sign in when they go.</li>
		<li>For quiz score throwdowns the average of all members of a small groups is taken. Make-ups are not included.</li>
	</ul>
</ul>
<p><b>These rules can be changed at any time by the PTA in charge of Small Group Wars. All issues are up to his/her discretion.</b></p>

<br>

<h2>Challenge another Small Group:</h2>
<ul>
	<li>To challenge another small group ask one of your PTAs to challenge the other group's PTAs. If a challenge is accepted, one of the PTA's must notify the PTA in charge of throwdowns.</li>
</ul>
